abstract: Profile of Crystal Dunn, United States women's national team soccer player who is quick and versatile; Dunn failed to make 2015 World Cup roster, but looks like lock for 2016 Olympics.
lead_paragraph: Dunn, the last U.S. player cut before last year’s World Cup, has become a prolific scorer and looks like a lock to play in the Olympics.

headline.main: Pint-Size Crystal Dunn Reaches New Heights With U.S. Soccer
headline.print_headline: A Young Talent Rises for the U.S. Women
